summary: A CyberTipline report submitted to the National Center for Missing & Exploited Children (NCMEC) alleging that Jeffrey Epstein's 'private group' is still active, with Jennifer Dee Young identified as the ringleader. The report was processed by NCMEC's Child Sex Trafficking Team and forwarded to the FBI.

events.title: CyberTipline Report Submission
events.description: An individual named Kathryn submits a report to NCMEC alleging child sex trafficking and that Epstein's private group remains active.

events.title: NCMEC Processing and FBI Referral
events.description: NCMEC's Child Sex Trafficking Team processes the report, conducts internal database searches, and makes it available to the FBI's Alexandria field office.

keyFacts: A 2020 CyberTipline report alleges Jeffrey Epstein's 'private group' was still active after his death, with Jennifer Dee Young identified as its ringleader.
The report was submitted by a person named Kathryn and classified by NCMEC as a 'Child Sex Trafficking' incident.
NCMEC analysts conducted searches on the reporter and the named individuals but found no prior matches in their databases at the time.
The report was forwarded to the FBI's field office in Alexandria, Virginia, for law enforcement follow-up.
The reporting party's narrative was described by NCMEC as 'disjointed and difficult to understand.'
